Admission is $10 for adults and $5 for students.

post_text: Parents: there has been an update regarding our travel plans. If your student tells you we are not leaving until tomorrow they are correct. All students need to be at the high school at 6:30 a.m. to load the bus. Shows still start at 1:00 p.m. and we are the last of 6 to perform. Return time will be determined by how well we do and how long it takes for all of the decisions to be made. Estimated return time will be between 1:00-2:00 a.m.

post_text: Red Devil Players did awesome at District OAP on Wednesday. Mariah Gaston, Cody Phillips and Cody Wyatt received Honorable Mention and Amye Templeton, Cat Ward and Andrew Hutchens received All-Star Cast. Diane Renteria was part of the All-Star Crew and the Rankin crew was named the Outstanding Technical Crew (Diane Renteria, Matthew Watson, Lesley Watson, Shania Valadez and Zoie Benitez). Next up is Bi-District on Wednesday & Thursday, April 1st & 2nd, at Van Horn. Performances start at 1:00 on Thursday and Rankin will be the last to perform.

post_text: The Red Devil Players facebook is up and going. Here you will find pictures from shows, important information about rehearsals and clinics, and results from contests. If you know students in either junior high or high school one-act play, please suggest this page to them since I don't 'friend' students until after they graduate. Also, if you know of anyone else who might be interested, please suggest the page. I'm looking forward to a fun and successful spring!
